						               													<description>A two-player abstract combat simulation.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the setup phase of the game, two sets of dominoes are used as &amp;quot;map tiles&amp;quot; to build the playing area (map/terrain), an 8x8 grid of spaces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the next phase, sets of dice are used as pieces (armies of varying strength) that move and battle on the board. A second set of dominoes (one complete set per player) are used as &amp;quot;action tiles&amp;quot; to manipulate the dice, performing movement, combat, building of fortifications and artillery, and bringing reinforcements onto the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when the players' stacks of action tiles are depleted.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Victory goes to whoever scores the most points. The most points are earned for dice (armies) that occupy the higher levels (hills) on the 3D board. Hence the name &amp;quot;Take the High Ground&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
